UPK - Ubuntu Package Kit

UPK is a unified CLI for managing packages across multiple package managers
on Ubuntu systems. It provides a single interface to search, install, update,
and remove packages from APT, Snap, Flatpak, Pacstall, and AppImage sources.

Usage:
  upk search <package-name>
  upk install <package-name>
  upk remove <package-name>
  upk list
  upk update

For more information, run:
  upk --help

Website: https://github.com/undefinederror/upk
